author: TOI Education
description: Rajasthan Board of Secondary Education (RBSE) will conduct board exams twice a year for Class 10 and 12 students starting from the 2026-27 academic session. The first exam is compulsory, while the second, optional session allows students to improve marks in up to three subjects, with the best performance considered for final results.
title: RBSE to conduct board exams twice a year from 2026‑27

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Russia launched a massive wave of drone and missile strikes, crippling Ukraine's energy infrastructure and reducing power generation to zero.  The state power company reported its facilities were completely knocked out, leading to widespread, prolonged power outages across multiple regions as repairs continue.
title: ‘War’s most challenging night’: Ukraine’s power generation at ‘zero’

author: RAMENDRA SINGH
description: Madhya Pradesh chief minister Mohan Yadav has assured that Munna Singh Gaud, the father of women’s World Cup–winning cricketer Kranti Gaud, will be reinstated as police constable. Gaud was dismissed in 2012 after an alleged error during election duty. The announcement came during Kranti’s felicitation ceremony in Bhopal, where the CM commended the bowler for bringing glory to the nation and her state.
title: World Cup magic: Kranti Gaud's win helps her father reclaim lost honour

author: SURENDRA SINGH
title: Interstellar visitor 3I/ATLAS loses tail, baffles astronomers about its identity

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Pakistan’s star batter Babar Azam added another feather to his illustrious career by completing 15,000 international runs during the third ODI against South Africa on Saturday. The milestone came in the series decider at Iqbal Stadium, Faisalabad, making Babar only the fifth Pakistani to achieve the landmark.
title: Babar Azam hits mega milestone! Joins Viv, Azharuddin and Cook in exclusive list

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Congress leader Rahul Gandhi claims the BJP has stolen votes in Haryana and other states. He alleges a centralized plan involving PM Modi, Amit Shah, and the Election Commission. Gandhi presented data on fake voter entries and duplicate photos. The BJP dismissed the claims as baseless and an attempt to defame institutions.
title: ‘Same method in MP, Chhattisgarh’: Rahul Gandhi escalates ‘vote theft’ charge; hits out at BJP, EC

author: SASWATI SARKAR
description: West Bengal's mandate for schools to sing the state anthem sparked pushback in Darjeeling, where the Gorkhaland Territorial Administration insisted on maintaining local Nepali anthems and prayers. This highlights how daily school rituals become arenas for negotiating language, identity, and belonging, revealing that shared citizenship doesn't necessitate uniform cultural symbols.
title: Uniformity vs identity: State anthem mandatory in WB schools; Darjeeling opts out

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Bollywood stars Katrina Kaif and Vicky Kaushal have joyfully welcomed their first child, a baby boy, into the world. The news was met with widespread congratulations from friends, family, and industry colleagues, including filmmaker Karan Johar. Vicky's brother, Sunny Kaushal, expressed his excitement about becoming an uncle, while Vicky's father, Sham Kaushal, shared his profound gratitude for the blessings.
title: Katrina Kaif, Vicky Kaushal welcome baby boy; Karan Johar extends his wishes

author: VIVEK NARAYANAN AND MALATHY IYER
description: Chaos unfolded at Cooper Hospital following the death of a patient, as the medical staff faced aggression from the deceased's son, leading to an assault on two doctors and an intern. In response, many resident doctors have chosen to go on mass casual leave, voicing their frustrations and fears.
title: Mumbai: Man assaults 3 Cooper Hospital doctors after mother’s death

author: TOI Astrology
description: Hindu astrology emphasizes Shubh Muhurat, auspicious times for new beginnings, believed to invite positive energy and divine blessings. November 9, 2025, falls within the sacred Margashirsha month, dedicated to Lord Vishnu, making it a spiritually significant day. Astrologer Vishal Bhardwaj outlines specific auspicious times for various zodiac signs on this day for different activities.
title: November 9: Best time today, as per zodiac sign

author: TNN
description: A tragic early morning accident on SG Road claimed the life of 23-year-old Aryan Batra after his speeding car collided with a stationary truck. Two 21-year-old women, passengers in Batra's car, were seriously injured, with one remaining unconscious. Police are investigating the circumstances, including the direction of travel and potential party attendance.
title: Death at dawn: 23-year-old dies as car rams parked truck in Ahmedabad; 2 women injured

author: TOI Education
description: Two Missouri school districts, Independence and Hallsville, have overwhelmingly won voter approval to continue their four-day school weeks. This marks a significant shift under a new law requiring public consent for non-rural districts. The move is seen as a boost for teacher recruitment and retention, with educators citing improved work-life balance and planning time.
title: 4-day school week gets community nod as Missouri voters back pilot districts

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Zarine Khan, wife of veteran actor Sanjay Khan and mother to Sussanne and Farah Khan Ali, passed away at 81. Her daughters shared deeply emotional tributes, remembering her grace, love, and as their guiding light. Zarine Khan's funeral was conducted according to Hindu traditions, attended by close family and friends.
title: Sussanne Khan pens emotional tribute to mom Zarine Khan: ‘You took our hearts’

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: A speeding car fleeing police crashed into a crowd outside a Tampa bar, killing four and injuring eleven. The driver, Silas Sampson, was attempting to evade law enforcement after street racing. This tragic incident has prompted renewed discussion on police pursuit policies.
title: Tampa tragedy: Speeding car fleeing police ploughs into crowd; four dead, 11 injured

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: A Railways employee was filmed discarding garbage from a moving train, leading to his immediate dismissal. The incident, captured on video by a passenger, sparked public outrage and renewed concerns about waste management within Indian Railways. The railway authorities have taken swift action, imposing penalties and initiating counseling for staff to prevent future occurrences.
title: Watch: Railways employee filmed by passenger throwing garbage from moving train

author: TNN
description: A 28-year-old Rapido bike-taxi driver was apprehended in Bengaluru for allegedly sexually harassing a 20-year-old woman during a ride. The victim shared her ordeal on Instagram, detailing how the driver attempted to grab her legs. Police initiated a case after her complaint, and the accused claims he was trying to rub his back.
title: Bengaluru rapido driver who 'tried to grab woman's legs' arrested

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: An Indian-origin US citizen, working for Illinois DOT, was questioned by masked federal agents about his immigration status and New York City Mayor Zohran Mamdani. Governor Pritzker condemned the incident as potential racial profiling. The Department of Homeland Security denied the agents were from ICE or CBP, but the event caused local alarm and school lockdowns.
title: Indian-origin man questioned in Chicago; governor says ‘because of his skin color’

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Pakistan cricketer Azam Khan has drawn a comparison between Babar Azam’s impact on Pakistan cricket and Virat Kohli’s influence on Indian cricket, highlighting how Babar transformed Pakistan’s image from a team known mainly for its fast bowlers to one celebrated for batting excellence — despite not having the same level of support that Kohli enjoyed during his rise.
title: Virat Kohli had Sachin Tendulkar, who was there with Babar Azam?’: Azam Khan's bold remark

author: TNN
description: A Pune businessman, inspired by crime fiction, meticulously planned and executed his wife's murder after suspecting an affair. He strangled her, cremated the body in a custom iron box, and scattered the ashes. Inconsistencies in his statements and call records ultimately led to his arrest, unraveling his chilling plot.
title: Pune man strangles wife, burns body in iron box; read crime novels before murder

author: MAHIMA ROY
description: New England Patriots star Stefon Diggs faces paternity claims from Aileen Lopera, with a test confirming him as the father, while also expecting a child with Cardi B. Amidst this, Diggs shared a cryptic social media quote about fate. DJ Akademiks also alleged Diggs fathered a child with K’yanna Barber.
title: Stefon Diggs Reacts After Being Named Father of Aileen Lopera’s Child

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: The Indian team had earlier declined to receive the Asia Cup winner’s trophy from PCB chief Mohsin Naqvi, who also serves as the Asian Cricket Council chairperson, citing his anti-India stance. Efforts are now underway to resolve the trophy dispute, with representatives from both cricket boards having met recently in Dubai.
title: Asia Cup: ‘Feels great to finally get to touch the trophy,’ says Suryakumar Yadav

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Pujara’s wife, Puja, recalled the incident in her book The Diary of a Cricketer’s Wife: “Destiny impelled him to dash heedlessly to a ball for a catch that was never there; and the result: a ruptured anterior cruciate ligament, an impending surgery and a temporarily halted cricketing career — all without playing a single game for KKR.”
title: Big revelation! When Shah Rukh Khan stepped in to save Cheteshwar Pujara's career

author: TNN
description: Videos of prisoners, including serial rapist Umesh Reddy and a terror case accused, using mobile phones inside Bengaluru's Central Prison have surfaced. This security lapse has prompted an inquiry into how the phones were provided and who is involved. Chief Minister Siddaramaiah has ordered a report and action against those responsible.
title: B'luru prison under fire: Serial rapist, IS handler caught using phones, watching TV; CM orders probe

author: NEWTON SEQUEIRA
description: A German travel influencer faced harassment in Goa when local rickshaw drivers demanded an exorbitant fare, forcing him to use the app-based GoaMiles. The situation escalated with threats, police intervention, and a fine for the GoaMiles driver, highlighting a growing turf war impacting tourism.
title: 'What’s the problem?': German tourist harassed by local cabbies in Goa

author: TNN
description: A 40-year-old technician was allegedly murdered by his wife in Jaipur during a domestic dispute. The 32-year-old accused reportedly used a grinding stone and pestle to strike her husband on the head, leading to his death. Neighbours alerted by the commotion transported the victim to the hospital, where he was declared dead on arrival.
title: Jaipur horror: Man bludgeoned to death with grinding stone, pestle by enraged wife

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Meta's Llama 4 AI model is being updated to address "left-leaning" political bias, a move distinct from traditional concerns. Meta claims this bias affects all leading LLMs, including those from Google and OpenAI, due to internet training data. Llama 4 reportedly refuses fewer controversial topics and offers more balanced responses, aiming for neutrality.
title: Mark Zuckerberg calls Altman, Pichai chatbots ‘problematic’, says Meta is fixing it

title: Richa appointed DSP in Bengal police
